WEBVTT

00:03.699 --> 00:04.047
.

00:04.091 --> 00:06.006
- Welcome to the CFD, Chaplain.

00:06.049 --> 00:08.356
- You two would actually
be great together.

00:08.399 --> 00:09.531
No.

00:09.574 --> 00:11.707
- I'm Benny's daughter, Katie.

00:11.750 --> 00:15.363
- I would like to ask Katie
out on a date.

00:15.406 --> 00:17.800
- Your father passed away
ten minutes ago.

00:17.843 --> 00:19.454
I'm so sorry.

00:19.497 --> 00:22.457
- Your father told Grissom
that I am the type of leader

00:22.500 --> 00:24.502
who molds good men
into great ones,

00:24.546 --> 00:26.287
and that you were
all the proof he needs

00:26.330 --> 00:28.767
to know that that's true.

00:32.771 --> 00:35.296
♪

00:35.339 --> 00:37.602
- No, I already checked
the garage.

00:40.866 --> 00:43.217
- Hey, look what I found.

00:44.522 --> 00:46.524
Check out
that handsome mug.

00:49.049 --> 00:51.529
- You box up everything
in the file cabinets?

00:51.573 --> 00:52.443
- Yeah.

00:52.487 --> 00:53.792
I mean, none of it's organized,

00:53.836 --> 00:55.751
but hopefully,
it has everything you need

00:55.794 --> 00:57.274
to settle the estate.

00:57.318 --> 01:00.582
- You didn't happen to find
a bronze medal, did you?

01:00.625 --> 01:02.105
- Um...

01:02.149 --> 01:03.933
- It'd be in a display box.

01:03.976 --> 01:06.675
"Carter Harrison Award
for Distinguished Service."

01:06.718 --> 01:08.111
- Sorry.

01:08.155 --> 01:10.070
♪

01:11.419 --> 01:14.335
He could have left it
with one of his exes.

01:14.378 --> 01:16.598
- Hard enough to see
those women at the service

01:16.641 --> 01:19.905
without having to go to them,
hat in hand.

01:19.949 --> 01:21.168
I'd rather just let this go.

01:21.211 --> 01:22.734
- I'll take care of it.

01:24.127 --> 01:25.868
Okay.

01:25.911 --> 01:30.438
♪

01:30.481 --> 01:32.875
- Benny used to talk about
being buried with the medal.

01:32.918 --> 01:34.094
♪

01:34.137 --> 01:36.226
- Well, maybe I can help.

01:36.270 --> 01:38.446
I mean, you already
have enough going on.

01:38.489 --> 01:40.404
- It's fine.

01:40.448 --> 01:42.145
- Kelly.

01:42.189 --> 01:45.148
Will--will you let me
help you with this?

01:45.192 --> 01:46.889
Please?

01:49.805 --> 01:50.762
Okay.

01:52.112 --> 01:53.548
Oh. Look.

01:53.591 --> 01:56.159
I got to get in
for shift, but, um...

01:56.203 --> 01:58.466
I'll check in later, okay?

02:01.121 --> 02:08.128
♪

02:09.825 --> 02:12.219
Hey.

02:14.046 --> 02:15.874
- Worse than he'll admit.

02:15.918 --> 02:18.616
He keeps taking point on all
the funeral arrangements.

02:18.660 --> 02:20.401
He won't let
anyone else near it.

02:20.444 --> 02:22.794
Uh, the service is Saturday,
by the way.

02:22.838 --> 02:24.448
- I'll make an announcement.

02:24.492 --> 02:26.146
Anything else we can do?

02:26.189 --> 02:27.886
- Maybe.

02:27.930 --> 02:29.236
Uh...

02:29.279 --> 02:33.153
Hey, you guys know
any of Benny's exes?

02:33.196 --> 02:35.633
- Uh, one or two, sort of.

02:35.677 --> 02:38.070
- Okay, I am on
a scavenger hunt

02:38.114 --> 02:39.550
for one of Benny's old medals,

02:39.594 --> 02:41.639
so I might need
to make a house call.

02:41.683 --> 02:43.989
- Hey, whatever you need,
we're here.

02:44.033 --> 02:46.296
- Thank you.

02:46.340 --> 02:48.646
- Hey, Cruz.

02:48.690 --> 02:50.474
You haven't heard anything
about Katie coming back

02:50.518 --> 02:52.172
for the funeral, have you?

02:52.215 --> 02:53.260
- Mm, hadn't thought
about that.

02:53.303 --> 02:54.522
No idea.

02:54.565 --> 02:56.132
- Squad three, ambo 61.
- Right.

02:56.176 --> 02:58.308
- Pin-in accident,
Harrison and Dearborn.

03:04.271 --> 03:11.539
♪

03:14.585 --> 03:15.630
- Help!

03:17.327 --> 03:18.546
Help!

03:19.373 --> 03:21.940
- Hang on, sweetie.
We're coming.

03:21.984 --> 03:24.291
Squad three, we have
a single vehicle accident.

03:24.334 --> 03:26.684
A toddler in a car seat
needs extrication.

03:26.728 --> 03:28.643
- Copy that, almost there.

03:28.686 --> 03:30.035
- He ran right out
in front of me.

03:30.079 --> 03:31.994
I--I couldn't see.

03:32.037 --> 03:39.001
♪

03:42.918 --> 03:48.228
♪

03:48.271 --> 03:49.925
- Hey, hey!
My little sister's in there.

03:49.968 --> 03:51.274
- All right, just stand back.
We'll get her out.

03:51.318 --> 03:52.580
- 61 to main,

03:52.623 --> 03:54.059
we have an additional victim,
pedestrian.

03:54.103 --> 03:56.279
We need another ambo ASAP.
- Copy, 61.

03:56.323 --> 03:59.151
Ambo 91
is just around the corner.

03:59.195 --> 04:00.718
- Help!
- Hang on.

04:00.762 --> 04:01.980
We're gonna
get you out, okay?

04:03.112 --> 04:08.509
♪

04:08.552 --> 04:11.120
- Capp, get the jaws!
- On it!

04:11.163 --> 04:12.600
- I've got a pulse.

04:12.643 --> 04:13.905
It's thready, but it's there.

04:17.126 --> 04:18.649
He's not responding.

04:18.693 --> 04:20.999
Let's board and collar him
so 91 can load and go.

04:21.043 --> 04:23.132
- I'm on it.

04:31.358 --> 04:32.837
- Help.
- Okay, all right.

04:32.881 --> 04:35.623
We're gonna help you.
Let me see your face.

04:37.494 --> 04:39.801
Hey, Brett,
we need you over here.

04:39.844 --> 04:41.324
Little girl might have glass
in her eyes.

04:41.368 --> 04:43.152
- All right, keep her still.

04:43.935 --> 04:47.069
- 61, we'll take over.
- Thanks.

04:47.112 --> 04:49.114
- Oh.

04:49.158 --> 04:50.290
- Oh, I know, I know.

04:50.333 --> 04:51.421
Here, look up, for me, sweetie.

04:51.465 --> 04:53.336
Let me see your face.

04:53.380 --> 04:54.642
- This is my parent's car.

04:54.685 --> 04:56.731
I--I think it's got
a blind spot.

04:56.774 --> 04:59.516
Just please tell me she's okay.

04:59.560 --> 05:00.865
- Her face is cut up a bit,

05:00.909 --> 05:03.128
but there's no glass
in her eyes.

05:03.172 --> 05:04.129
♪

05:04.173 --> 05:05.479
Hey.

05:05.522 --> 05:07.437
- Let's give her space,
check you out,

05:07.481 --> 05:08.786
make sure you're not injured.

05:08.830 --> 05:10.658
- All right.
You're gonna be all right.

05:10.701 --> 05:12.007
We're just gonna
have to get a doctor

05:12.050 --> 05:14.139
to take a look at you, okay?
- No!

05:14.183 --> 05:16.228
That's my sister's.

05:16.272 --> 05:18.535
She said I need to hold it.

05:18.579 --> 05:20.755
♪

05:22.017 --> 05:23.497
- Yeah.

05:23.540 --> 05:30.504
♪

05:30.547 --> 05:33.202
- I got you, I got you.

05:33.245 --> 05:40.470
♪

05:55.833 --> 05:56.834
- I snagged
some extra washcloths

05:56.878 --> 05:58.445
from the supply room.

05:58.488 --> 06:02.057
Should come in handy if we
go on any bar runs tonight.

06:02.100 --> 06:04.015
- Great, thanks.

06:06.191 --> 06:07.236
- Poor kid.

06:07.279 --> 06:09.412
The crash must
have her shaken up.

06:09.456 --> 06:11.719
- Yeah.

06:13.764 --> 06:16.245
- So, your pedestrian,
Mr. Torres, he just came to.

06:16.288 --> 06:18.900
Still in A-fib, but that's
consistent with his history.

06:18.943 --> 06:20.684
Nothing we can't manage
with medication.

06:20.728 --> 06:22.904
He's got two broken legs,
a broken wrist,

06:22.947 --> 06:25.515
and a nasty headache,
but he's recovering.

06:25.559 --> 06:27.169
- Thanks.

06:27.212 --> 06:29.737
If anything changes, do you
mind giving me a heads up?

06:29.780 --> 06:32.740
- Will do.
Excuse me.

06:34.481 --> 06:36.047
- Okay, spill.

06:36.091 --> 06:38.310
What's got your head
in the clouds?

06:40.617 --> 06:43.577
- It's something
the little girl said.

06:43.620 --> 06:45.579
She told me her sister
handed her her phone

06:45.622 --> 06:47.581
and asked her to keep it.

06:47.624 --> 06:48.973
It wasn't clear,

06:49.017 --> 06:51.715
but it sounded like
she meant after the crash.

06:54.588 --> 06:56.590
I think the driver
might have been texting

06:56.633 --> 06:58.200
when she hit that man.

06:58.243 --> 07:05.294
♪

07:09.777 --> 07:10.865
- A little off-course

07:10.908 --> 07:12.736
for the fueling depot,
aren't we?

07:12.780 --> 07:14.738
- Kidd needs to make
a quick pit stop.

07:14.782 --> 07:16.174
- Thanks for the detour,
Captain.

07:16.218 --> 07:18.307
Hey, remind me.
Which one in this?

07:18.350 --> 07:20.483
- Ex number four.

07:20.527 --> 07:22.006
- Sweet of you all to come by,

07:22.050 --> 07:24.792
but someone already came
to tell me about Benny.

07:24.835 --> 07:26.750
It's hard to believe.

07:26.794 --> 07:28.056
Always seemed like that man

07:28.099 --> 07:30.493
was the perfect
physical specimen.

07:30.537 --> 07:32.843
- It was a shock to everyone.

07:32.887 --> 07:36.412
- I'd offer you a pour
if you weren't on duty.

07:36.456 --> 07:40.721
You know, Benny and I actually
met back when I was bartending.

07:40.764 --> 07:42.200
He used to come by regular

07:42.244 --> 07:45.203
just to charm me
with that silver tongue of his.

07:46.074 --> 07:47.162
It worked.

07:47.205 --> 07:49.991
- Um, well, we were wondering

07:50.034 --> 07:55.300
if Benny left anything behind
after you two broke up.

07:55.344 --> 07:56.780
- Probably.

07:56.824 --> 07:59.043
We were off and on
for a while in there.

07:59.087 --> 08:01.524
We'd be fighting
like cats and dogs one day,

08:01.568 --> 08:04.832
then be making up like a couple
of bunny rabbits the next.

08:04.875 --> 08:07.835
Firefighters, am I right?

08:07.878 --> 08:09.663
- Is there--is there a chance

08:09.706 --> 08:12.317
you might have seen
a medal he won?

08:12.361 --> 08:13.536
Like

08:13.580 --> 08:15.538
- Mm, not that I can think of.

08:15.582 --> 08:18.280
But if I stumble on it,
I promise I'll let y'all know.

08:18.323 --> 08:21.196
- The thing is,
is we don't have time to wait.

08:21.239 --> 08:24.155
Um, this award,
it's for the funeral.

08:24.199 --> 08:26.157
- Oh.

08:26.201 --> 08:28.464
Sure.

08:28.508 --> 08:32.555
To be honest, I don't know
if I'm gonna make it to that.

08:32.599 --> 08:34.644
I hate to sound shallow,
I just--

08:34.688 --> 08:36.907
I try to stay as positive
as possible.

08:36.951 --> 08:39.823
Too much negativity
is bad for the blood, you know?

08:39.867 --> 08:44.567
But, listen, if you
want to swing by later,

08:44.611 --> 08:49.398
maybe you and I can
spend some time looking for it.

08:49.441 --> 08:52.053
♪

08:52.096 --> 08:55.578
- Uh, hey, Casey, remember,
we have that thing.

08:55.622 --> 08:57.014
- Yeah.

08:57.058 --> 08:58.581
- Right, right,
right, right, right.

08:58.625 --> 09:01.236
The, uh--the drill.
both: The drill, the drill.

09:01.279 --> 09:03.934
- Drill. Um...

09:03.978 --> 09:06.720
Thank you for your
hospitality, ma'am.

09:06.763 --> 09:08.809
- Penelope, please.

09:08.852 --> 09:10.593
- Yep.

09:10.637 --> 09:16.730
♪

09:16.773 --> 09:19.559
- You have to say something in
your run sheet, though, right?

09:19.602 --> 09:21.517
Not necessarily.

09:21.561 --> 09:23.519
I'm supposed to report
her medical condition,

09:23.563 --> 09:24.651
not the cause of the accident.

09:24.694 --> 09:26.130
That's out of my lane.

09:26.174 --> 09:29.264
- No one's asking you
to be judge and jury.

09:29.307 --> 09:31.919
All you gotta do
is report what you heard.

09:31.962 --> 09:35.009
Let someone else
worry about the rest.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.236
- Chief.

09:48.283 --> 09:49.589
Thanks for this.

09:49.632 --> 09:51.416
- Least I could do.

09:51.460 --> 09:52.809
How you feeling?

09:54.245 --> 09:56.639
- Got tons to do,
not much time.

09:56.683 --> 09:58.119
- That's not what I mean.

09:58.162 --> 10:00.817
- He's ready to see you.

10:03.167 --> 10:05.474
- My father had a 35-year
career in the department.

10:05.517 --> 10:08.085
He led one of the busiest
battalions in his district

10:08.129 --> 10:09.783
and won the CFD's
highest honors.

10:09.826 --> 10:11.219
If anybody deserves

10:11.262 --> 10:13.656
a full-scale department
sendoff, it's him.

10:13.700 --> 10:15.876
- I wholeheartedly agree.

10:15.919 --> 10:18.356
The man was a legend
in his time.

10:21.098 --> 10:23.274
- I'm sorry for your loss.

10:23.318 --> 10:25.973
Commissioner Grissom
sends his sincere condolences.

10:26.016 --> 10:28.715
- Right, I got the letter.

10:28.758 --> 10:31.369
- I'm just talking
real-world here.

10:31.413 --> 10:34.982
We can arrange an official
color guard, without question.

10:35.025 --> 10:36.287
Attendance of senior officers

10:36.331 --> 10:37.854
is something I can try
and coordinate--

10:41.902 --> 10:45.906
- A full-scale funeral
with a municipal parade?

10:45.949 --> 10:47.516
That's gonna be out of reach.

10:47.559 --> 10:50.127
Those arrangements
are strictly reserved

10:50.171 --> 10:51.999
for line-of-duty deaths.

10:52.042 --> 10:55.959
♪

10:56.003 --> 10:58.353
I'm sorry, my hands are tied.

10:58.396 --> 11:01.573
- We appreciate
the consideration.

11:03.445 --> 11:05.360
- It's hard to imagine
a veteran firefighter

11:05.403 --> 11:07.014
who dedicated his life
to this department

11:07.057 --> 11:08.711
gets nothing but a flag
and a "thank you."

11:08.755 --> 11:10.147
- Look, I understand
your frustration,

11:10.191 --> 11:11.845
but we are talking
the distinction

11:11.888 --> 11:13.411
for active-duty deaths.

11:13.455 --> 11:14.586
That's sacred ground.

11:14.630 --> 11:16.414
You had to know that
that was a long shot.

11:16.458 --> 11:18.852
- He deserves better than this.

11:18.895 --> 11:20.288
- Look.

11:20.331 --> 11:22.246
Why don't you
come by the house?

11:22.290 --> 11:24.814
Have lunch, be with your people
for an hour.

11:24.858 --> 11:27.425
- I get what you're trying
to do, Chief, really,

11:27.469 --> 11:28.818
but I'm fine.

11:28.862 --> 11:30.733
I got things to do.

11:30.777 --> 11:34.868
♪

11:34.911 --> 11:37.914
Thank you for
backing me up on this.

11:38.872 --> 11:41.048
- If there is anything
that you need,

11:41.091 --> 11:43.528
you come to me straightaway,
you understand?

11:43.572 --> 11:45.400
- Will do, Chief.

11:45.443 --> 11:50.492
♪

11:54.583 --> 11:54.714
.

11:54.757 --> 11:57.499
- You're yanking my chain.
She actually said that?

11:57.542 --> 11:59.196
What'd you do?
- We got the heck out of there

11:59.240 --> 12:01.285
before she jumped
Casey's bones.

12:01.329 --> 12:03.244
- It was uncomfortable.

12:03.287 --> 12:04.854
- Hey, you are
more than welcome

12:04.898 --> 12:06.334
to come to the next one.

12:06.377 --> 12:08.902
I'm planning on visiting
ex number three today.

12:10.120 --> 12:12.644
- No, that's number two,
I think?

12:12.688 --> 12:14.124
Or was it--
- Yeah, it depends

12:14.168 --> 12:15.386
if you're just talking
about wives.

12:15.430 --> 12:16.692
- Right.
- Guys, if you want to fall

12:16.736 --> 12:18.346
down the rabbit hole
of Benny's love life,

12:18.389 --> 12:19.739
it's a long way to the bottom.

12:19.782 --> 12:21.349
Let's just focus
on the plan for today, huh?

12:21.392 --> 12:23.220
- Yes, I'll pick you up
in a couple hours,

12:23.264 --> 12:24.874
and we'll drive
to Kenosha together, yeah?

12:24.918 --> 12:27.094
- All right, copy that.
See you in a few.

12:27.137 --> 12:28.748
- Cool.

12:35.145 --> 12:36.799
- Brett.

12:36.843 --> 12:38.627
It's 7:30.
I need your report.

12:38.670 --> 12:40.890
- I'm reviewing them now,
Chief, sorry.

12:42.065 --> 12:44.459
- Gentleman.
- Wallace.

12:44.502 --> 12:46.591
- Thanks for showing up.

12:58.560 --> 13:01.693
- So I'm giving this talk
at a conference once, right?

13:01.737 --> 13:06.176
Step off the stage, the SOB
corners me in the hall,

13:06.220 --> 13:09.179
and I swear to God--boom!

13:09.223 --> 13:11.486
Cold-cocks me
out of the blue.

13:11.529 --> 13:14.576
Turns out, Benny caught wind
that some instructor

13:14.619 --> 13:17.100
was putting the screws
to his kid down at the academy.

13:17.144 --> 13:18.406
The damn lughead,

13:18.449 --> 13:19.886
he was looking
for Chief Cochran.

13:22.802 --> 13:25.195
Oh, that was Benny, though.

13:25.239 --> 13:27.284
He was a scrapper,

13:27.328 --> 13:28.764
especially when it came
to his kid.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.505
- For good reason:
Kelly Severide

13:30.548 --> 13:33.073
is one of the best firefighters
I have seen in my career.

13:33.116 --> 13:34.901
- Agreed.

13:34.944 --> 13:37.860
- Which is why I was hoping...

13:37.904 --> 13:42.647
that this department
would show up for him.

13:42.691 --> 13:44.258
You all know

13:44.301 --> 13:46.651
the memorial service
is this Saturday, right--

13:46.695 --> 13:47.957
- Chief.

13:48.001 --> 13:51.613
I realize you've spoken
to CFD affairs.

13:51.656 --> 13:54.964
You understand that this is
completely out of our control?

13:55.008 --> 13:56.270
- Hear me out.

13:56.313 --> 13:58.446
I am not asking for the world.

13:58.489 --> 13:59.795
No parade.

13:59.839 --> 14:02.232
I am just asking
for a show of support.

14:02.276 --> 14:05.235
As many chiefs as possible,
a room full of dress blues.

14:05.279 --> 14:07.890
I mean, for God's sake,
something.

14:07.934 --> 14:12.590
Something that honors
what the name Severide means

14:12.634 --> 14:14.897
to this city
and this department.

14:17.944 --> 14:20.424
♪

14:20.468 --> 14:22.774
I'm just asking.

14:26.517 --> 14:28.302
- I don't know why
I kept any of it.

14:29.433 --> 14:30.652
My therapist, at the time,

14:30.695 --> 14:32.088
told me that closure
was a myth,

14:32.132 --> 14:34.612
and I took that to mean
maybe it wasn't over.

14:34.656 --> 14:36.484
Maybe Benny was coming back.

14:36.527 --> 14:38.138
Maybe he didn't just disappear

14:38.181 --> 14:40.923
on a permanent fishing trip
without a word of notice.

14:40.967 --> 14:43.665
- We--we're--we're sorry
for your loss, Beth.

14:43.708 --> 14:45.623
We were just wondering if--
- Like this!

14:45.667 --> 14:46.973
What am I supposed
to do with this?

14:47.016 --> 14:48.539
- Oh, actually, those have
pretty decent

14:48.583 --> 14:49.976
resale value
if you ever wanted to--

14:50.019 --> 14:52.935
- What kind of man
walks out on his two stepsons?

14:52.979 --> 14:55.764
Left those boys waiting for him
at soccer practice.

14:55.807 --> 14:57.505
And did you see the kind
of woman he left me for?

14:57.548 --> 14:59.333
That Penelope?

14:59.376 --> 15:00.421
both: Yeah.

15:00.464 --> 15:01.857
both: No.

15:03.990 --> 15:07.123
- The last thing we want to do
is reopen old wounds.

15:07.167 --> 15:08.646
We're just trying to find

15:08.690 --> 15:10.474
the one item
to memorialize him with.

15:10.518 --> 15:12.476
- Hmm, I should get the stack

15:12.520 --> 15:14.261
of unpaid bills
he left behind, then.

15:14.304 --> 15:17.917
- Well, we're doing this for
Kelly more than anyone else.

15:19.353 --> 15:20.920
- Right.

15:20.963 --> 15:23.009
Kelly.

15:23.052 --> 15:24.662
How's he doing?

15:25.620 --> 15:27.143
- He's struggling...

15:27.187 --> 15:28.623
but the--finding this medal,

15:28.666 --> 15:30.755
it would be a big help to him.

15:31.452 --> 15:33.541
- Kelly was always good to me.

15:33.584 --> 15:37.197
When Benny left, he understood.

15:37.240 --> 15:40.722
Helped validate that
it wasn't all in my head.

15:40.765 --> 15:41.766
- Mm.

15:43.420 --> 15:45.118
- I haven't seen anything like
what you're describing, though.

15:45.161 --> 15:46.293
I'm sorry.

15:46.336 --> 15:47.816
- It's okay.

15:47.859 --> 15:50.906
We appreciate you trying
to find it all the same.

15:50.950 --> 15:53.169
- Please give Kelly
my condolences.

15:53.213 --> 15:55.606
I know how much his father
meant to him.

15:55.650 --> 15:57.217
- We will.
- Hm.

15:57.260 --> 15:58.479
- Thanks.

15:58.522 --> 16:00.350
- You know,
if you aren't interested

16:00.394 --> 16:02.004
in that Dremel tool anymore,
I would--

16:02.048 --> 16:03.571
- Mouch!

16:10.926 --> 16:12.710
- Yeah.

16:12.754 --> 16:14.234
I just thought I'd swing by

16:14.277 --> 16:16.410
and check on that accident
victim from yesterday.

16:16.453 --> 16:17.628
- He's recovering well.

16:17.672 --> 16:19.065
Heart rate stabilizing
with the meds,

16:19.108 --> 16:21.589
and ortho says his fractures
aren't too bad.

16:21.632 --> 16:23.243
It helps that he's had
a few visitors

16:23.286 --> 16:24.722
here looking out for him.

16:26.724 --> 16:28.422
Holler if you
need something, okay?

16:28.465 --> 16:29.901
- Sure.

16:35.559 --> 16:37.605
Uh, Mr. and Mrs. Ballard?

16:37.648 --> 16:38.998
I'm Silvie Brett.
I'm the paramedic

16:39.041 --> 16:40.260
who treated your daughters
yesterday.

16:40.303 --> 16:41.261
- Oh!
- Oh, my God.

16:41.304 --> 16:42.697
Yes, hello.

16:42.740 --> 16:44.916
Thank you so much
for looking after our girls.

16:44.960 --> 16:46.440
- But how's
your little one doing?

16:46.483 --> 16:48.616
- Oh, she's almost
fully recovered.

16:48.659 --> 16:51.793
Erica, though, you know,
she's still shaken.

16:51.836 --> 16:53.795
She feels responsible.

16:53.838 --> 16:58.060
- Um, has she been here
with you visiting Mr. Torres?

16:58.104 --> 17:00.062
- Yes.
It was her idea, actually.

17:00.106 --> 17:03.457
- Erica set up a GoFundMe page
to help with his medical bills.

17:03.500 --> 17:05.981
She's poured
all of herself into it.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.461
- I, um--

17:07.504 --> 17:11.378
- We owe you everything...

17:11.421 --> 17:13.510
for saving our girls.

17:13.554 --> 17:17.123
From the bottom of our hearts,
thank you.

17:17.166 --> 17:18.646
♪

17:21.518 --> 17:23.390
- Here we are.

17:23.433 --> 17:27.481
Benjamin preselected
item number 232.

17:27.524 --> 17:29.526
"Eternal Remembrance."

17:29.570 --> 17:31.702
It's a lovely casket.

17:31.746 --> 17:33.835
Solid elm with a soft,
velvet interior--

17:33.878 --> 17:35.576
- Whatever he wanted.

17:38.318 --> 17:40.494
- Also preplanned
and reserved.

17:40.537 --> 17:42.931
All that's required
is final payment.

17:43.845 --> 17:45.890
- It's fine.

17:46.674 --> 17:48.676
Whatever it is,
I'll settle it now.

17:48.719 --> 17:51.505
- Now, regarding
the service...

17:52.767 --> 17:54.160
- If you want to submit a few

17:54.203 --> 17:56.162
family photos
for the slideshow--

17:56.205 --> 17:57.511
- No, you can skip that.

17:57.554 --> 18:00.340
- It doesn't have to be
anything too fancy.

18:00.383 --> 18:01.515
- Just run the card.

18:04.387 --> 18:05.475
- Understood.

18:05.519 --> 18:12.743
♪

18:22.188 --> 18:22.405
.

18:32.415 --> 18:35.288
Sylvie, uh, come on in.
Excuse the mess.

18:35.331 --> 18:36.898
I'm getting
my thoughts together

18:36.941 --> 18:37.986
for the memorial service.

18:38.029 --> 18:39.248
You caught me in the zone.

18:39.292 --> 18:41.294
- No, please.

18:41.337 --> 18:42.469
I'm glad you came.

18:42.512 --> 18:45.472
Uh, grab a seat
while I straighten up.

18:45.515 --> 18:47.387
- I'm--I'm not even sure
if this is something

18:47.430 --> 18:49.084
you can really
help me out with.

18:49.128 --> 18:52.261
- Well, I accept the challenge.

18:52.305 --> 18:54.133
So...

18:55.395 --> 18:56.526
what's on your mind?

18:59.050 --> 19:00.835
- I'm just wondering...

19:02.228 --> 19:06.449
Is it wrong to lie by omission?

19:06.493 --> 19:09.496
Even if you're not sure you
know what you think you know,

19:09.539 --> 19:11.019
and maybe someone
could get hurt

19:11.062 --> 19:12.499
if you say what
you think you know,

19:12.542 --> 19:15.589
but you're not really sure
if you actually know it?

19:17.243 --> 19:18.200
Uh...

19:18.244 --> 19:21.072
I--I need more.
- Okay, um...

19:21.116 --> 19:24.511
I--I got called to this
car wreck yesterday.

19:24.554 --> 19:27.296
A teenage driver
hit a pedestrian.

19:27.340 --> 19:29.211
I think she was texting
when it happened,

19:29.255 --> 19:31.082
but I'm not 100% certain.

19:31.126 --> 19:33.041
- Yes.

19:33.084 --> 19:35.174
In the hands of her
four-year-old sister.

19:35.217 --> 19:37.132
When I tried to take
the phone away,

19:37.176 --> 19:38.699
the toddler told me
her older sister

19:38.742 --> 19:40.744
made her promise to hold it.

19:40.788 --> 19:43.051
I think she meant
after the crash,

19:43.094 --> 19:44.313
but I can't be sure.

19:46.576 --> 19:47.882
Nothing.

19:47.925 --> 19:49.840
It's too busy
tying itself in knots.

19:49.884 --> 19:52.408
It just feels awful.

19:52.452 --> 19:54.497
I've never held something
like this in before.

19:54.541 --> 19:57.979
But if you saw the look
in this little girl's eyes,

19:58.022 --> 20:00.590
the way she and her sister
needed each other...

20:00.634 --> 20:04.464
I don't want to tear them apart
based on nothing but a hunch.

20:04.507 --> 20:06.379
♪

20:06.422 --> 20:08.946
- The Good Book's
got some wisdom on this.

20:08.990 --> 20:12.036
"He who makes haste
with his feet, errs."

20:12.080 --> 20:15.388
I'm paraphrasing,
but the gist of it is this.

20:15.431 --> 20:18.260
Take the time you need
to consider the facts,

20:18.304 --> 20:23.134
separate out your fears,
and trust your heart.

20:23.178 --> 20:24.614
♪

20:24.658 --> 20:26.442
You can't go wrong with that.

20:26.486 --> 20:29.097
♪

20:29.140 --> 20:31.230
- You're good at this.

20:33.232 --> 20:35.277
- The thing is...

20:35.321 --> 20:38.280
Katie and I didn't even
get a chance to say good-bye.

20:38.324 --> 20:39.281
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah.

20:39.325 --> 20:40.761
It was really chaotic.

20:40.804 --> 20:43.851
You know, it was a real
hurricane of emotion.

20:43.894 --> 20:45.287
- For sure.

20:45.331 --> 20:46.854
- I'm not making excuses.

20:46.897 --> 20:48.116
I'm not saying that I did

20:48.159 --> 20:51.554
everything right,
but I've grown.

20:51.598 --> 20:54.122
Being with Lily,
it's--it's really matured me.

20:54.165 --> 20:57.168
Oh, God, Lily.

20:57.212 --> 20:58.387
What am I going to say to her?

21:00.346 --> 21:01.956
You think Lily's
going to feel threatened?

21:01.999 --> 21:04.175
You think I should get out
ahead of this thing beforehand.

21:04.219 --> 21:06.047
Right, what would you say
to Chloe?

21:08.354 --> 21:10.356
- Oh!

21:10.399 --> 21:11.966
- No!

21:12.009 --> 21:13.228
- Come on, Cruz.

21:13.272 --> 21:14.795
I'm really
struggling here, man.

21:14.838 --> 21:17.798
- Otis, you need to breathe.

21:17.841 --> 21:19.800
This was four years ago.

21:19.843 --> 21:21.410
This doesn't have to be a thing

21:21.454 --> 21:24.674
unless you make it
a thing, all right?

21:24.718 --> 21:26.110
Just be yourself.

21:26.154 --> 21:28.504
Be glad to see her.

21:33.074 --> 21:35.685
- This is April Nolan,
Katie's mom.

21:35.729 --> 21:37.774
- Nah.

21:37.818 --> 21:39.341
Wouldn't want her to tell us
not to come.

21:39.385 --> 21:42.039
- Casey, if we
strike out on this,

21:42.083 --> 21:43.911
I'm ready
to keep searching, okay?

21:43.954 --> 21:46.653
Friends, relatives, anyone.

21:46.696 --> 21:48.785
I just can't go back
to Kelly empty-handed.

21:48.829 --> 21:50.352
- I wouldn't fret.

21:50.396 --> 21:53.312
I'd say the odds are about 90%
April has the medal.

21:53.355 --> 21:55.966
- No doubt in my mind.

21:57.446 --> 21:59.709
- The power
of positive thinking.

22:02.103 --> 22:04.235
- That's Katie
in her new restaurant.

22:04.279 --> 22:06.455
I forget the name.
It's something French.

22:06.499 --> 22:09.371
- Well, you must be very proud.

22:09.415 --> 22:12.331
- I sell those.

22:12.374 --> 22:15.725
I have an arrangement
with a designer in Kankakee.

22:15.769 --> 22:17.771
- It's...
- It's nice.

22:17.814 --> 22:19.381
- I can cut you a deal

22:19.425 --> 22:21.688
if you want to buy them in bulk
for the firehouse.

22:21.731 --> 22:24.386
Something to think about.
- Um...

22:24.430 --> 22:26.954
- I also make jewelry,
floral arrangements.

22:26.997 --> 22:31.045
I've dabbled in interior design
as you can probably see.

22:31.088 --> 22:32.786
Let me get you guys some cards.

22:32.829 --> 22:36.398
You know, Benny was one
of my initial investors.

22:36.442 --> 22:38.661
I think he was
trying to make amends

22:38.705 --> 22:41.708
for not being around
while Katie was growing up.

22:41.751 --> 22:43.927
He really helped me
process a lot.

22:43.971 --> 22:46.408
To forgive, and...

22:46.452 --> 22:50.543
- Uh, it's funny
you mention jewelry,

22:50.586 --> 22:54.242
because it's kind of in
the family of why we're here.

22:54.285 --> 22:57.419
Um, is there any chance

22:57.463 --> 23:02.337
that Benny left behind
an old medal?

23:03.294 --> 23:05.558
- Oh, my goodness, yes!

23:05.601 --> 23:08.256
I can't believe you guys
are looking for that.

23:08.299 --> 23:10.432
I'll be right back.

23:10.476 --> 23:13.000
- Oh, my God.
- All right, good.

23:15.481 --> 23:18.266
- It seemed like such
a silly thing to keep around,

23:18.309 --> 23:20.181
but something
in the back of my mind

23:20.224 --> 23:21.530
told me this had value.

23:21.574 --> 23:24.185
Take a look.
Isn't that something?

23:24.228 --> 23:26.317
You're welcome to it.

23:26.361 --> 23:31.758
♪

23:31.801 --> 23:33.716
- Actually, um...

23:33.760 --> 23:38.504
uh, we're looking for
an old firefighter medal.

23:38.547 --> 23:39.896
- Oh.

23:39.940 --> 23:42.638
That's the only medal I have.

23:42.682 --> 23:49.471
♪

23:49.515 --> 23:51.473
- Hey.
- Hey.

23:55.999 --> 23:57.784
He's a bit wrecked,
went to bed.

23:57.827 --> 24:01.352
- I should probably
do the same, then.

24:01.396 --> 24:03.659
- Oh, don't feel like
you have to.

24:06.445 --> 24:08.969
- Uh, surreal.

24:09.012 --> 24:10.710
It's funny.

24:10.753 --> 24:12.146
Benny spent all his life

24:12.189 --> 24:14.801
improvising from
one day to the next,

24:14.844 --> 24:18.935
but when it came to his death,
he had it all planned out.

24:18.979 --> 24:20.850
Kelly's running himself ragged,

24:20.894 --> 24:24.027
trying to do everything
exactly how Benny wanted.

24:25.638 --> 24:28.771
I don't know if
it's about contrition

24:28.815 --> 24:31.513
or closure or what.

24:31.557 --> 24:33.646
I'm glad he has you to rely on.

24:33.689 --> 24:35.778
♪

24:35.822 --> 24:39.129
- I'm--I'm barely
doing anything.

24:39.173 --> 24:42.176
- Oh, you're doing enough.

24:42.219 --> 24:45.527
I'm sure Kelly
would tell you himself,

24:45.571 --> 24:48.530
but he's lousy expressing
things like that.

24:51.490 --> 24:54.405
- You're good for him, Stella.
It's easy to see.

24:54.449 --> 24:56.756
♪

24:56.799 --> 24:58.192
- Thanks.

24:58.235 --> 24:59.236
- The way you've
been there for him,

24:59.280 --> 25:00.542
helping him find this medal,

25:00.586 --> 25:02.762
means more than you know.

25:02.805 --> 25:09.551
♪

25:13.163 --> 25:13.555
.

25:13.599 --> 25:15.601
- Hey, Brett.
- Morning, Chief.

25:15.644 --> 25:17.167
- I just got a call
from Chief Hatcher

25:17.211 --> 25:19.474
says you have a run sheet
open from last shift?

25:19.518 --> 25:21.432
- Right.

25:22.782 --> 25:25.436
- It's just a detail
from that first call.

25:25.480 --> 25:27.656
I needed time to clear it up.

25:31.181 --> 25:34.445
- Ambo 61, person down
from unknown causes.

25:34.489 --> 25:35.882
- Close it before lunch.

25:35.925 --> 25:37.971
No excuses.
- Yes, Chief.

25:43.977 --> 25:50.984
♪

25:52.725 --> 25:54.204
- Thank God you're here.

25:54.248 --> 25:55.815
I swear it was an accident.

25:56.685 --> 25:58.034
- Well, we were yelling,

25:58.078 --> 25:59.601
and the threw
the thing at me,

25:59.645 --> 26:02.212
so I threw it back
at him, and...

26:02.256 --> 26:03.692
- Help, please.

26:03.736 --> 26:05.955
Help, please.

26:07.566 --> 26:13.180
♪

26:13.223 --> 26:14.616
- Lungs are clear.

26:14.660 --> 26:16.096
We can't load him
on the rig like this, though.

26:16.139 --> 26:17.793
- Should we call
for a truck's help?

26:17.837 --> 26:20.317
- No, here, I got it.

26:20.361 --> 26:21.928
Stabilize that.

26:21.971 --> 26:23.146
Don't move.

26:23.190 --> 26:29.544
♪

26:29.588 --> 26:31.024
Easy.

26:31.067 --> 26:32.199
Almost done.

26:33.853 --> 26:35.985
- Smart.
- All right.

26:36.029 --> 26:38.597
Get an IV started.
I'll stabilized the prongs.

26:41.164 --> 26:42.557
- Hang in there, Howard.

26:42.601 --> 26:44.124
These ladies
are taking good care of you.

26:44.167 --> 26:46.953
We had a little argument
about yard care.

26:46.996 --> 26:50.304
- I didn't rake my dang leaves
onto your yard, Paul!

26:51.958 --> 26:53.742
You think I snuck around
in the dead of night

26:53.786 --> 26:55.396
to rake them
back into my own yard?

26:55.439 --> 26:56.658
- Just get this thing out of me

26:56.702 --> 26:58.704
so I can lodge it
into his damn skull!

26:58.747 --> 27:01.707
- No, sir, unless you are
going to help calm him down,

27:01.750 --> 27:03.230
I need you to step back.

27:03.273 --> 27:08.670
♪

27:08.714 --> 27:11.978
- Okay, Howard.

27:12.021 --> 27:16.025
I raked them into my yard
to prove a point.

27:16.069 --> 27:18.158
I just wanted you to trim
the darn thing back.

27:18.201 --> 27:20.377
I never meant for things
to get so out of hand.

27:20.421 --> 27:22.031
- I knew it.

27:25.818 --> 27:27.776
- 3rd place finish,

27:27.820 --> 27:31.650
2004 Master Anglers Tournament,
Calumet Harbor.

27:31.693 --> 27:33.260
- That's a big tournament.

27:33.303 --> 27:35.479
Might still be worth
including in the service.

27:38.395 --> 27:39.745
- No luck.

27:39.788 --> 27:42.443
I exhausted my contacts,
anyone who knew Benny.

27:42.486 --> 27:44.140
No one's seen the medal.

27:44.184 --> 27:47.056
- You think, uh--
you think, maybe,

27:47.100 --> 27:49.668
we could ask HQ
to press a new one?

27:49.711 --> 27:50.886
- Those things
are one-of-a-kind.

27:50.930 --> 27:53.062
CFD would never allow it.

27:55.282 --> 27:57.414
- Oh, my God.

27:57.458 --> 28:00.287
- Hey, Kidd.

28:02.724 --> 28:05.727
- You did what you could.

28:05.771 --> 28:07.947
He'll understand.

28:09.905 --> 28:12.212
- No, that's not it, ugh.

28:12.255 --> 28:14.910
Hey--hey, Capp,
grab me the needle scaler.

28:15.868 --> 28:17.652
- Uh, he's not around.

28:20.568 --> 28:23.527
- Whoa, Katie, hey.

28:23.571 --> 28:25.181
- Hey.

28:25.225 --> 28:26.356
- You're here.

28:26.400 --> 28:27.662
- Thought that was you.

28:27.706 --> 28:29.359
- Uh, I didn't realize

28:29.403 --> 28:31.361
you were coming to the house.

28:31.405 --> 28:33.886
Kelly's, uh...

28:33.929 --> 28:36.105
gone, took the shift off.

28:36.149 --> 28:37.324
- No, I know.

28:37.367 --> 28:40.066
I actually came to visit
the rest of you all.

28:40.109 --> 28:43.330
- Oh. Good.

28:45.898 --> 28:47.987
- Colorado is great.

28:48.030 --> 28:51.251
Beautiful skies, fresh air.

28:51.294 --> 28:52.948
I'm working as a sous chef

28:52.992 --> 28:54.907
in a new restaurant
in Boulder.

28:54.950 --> 28:55.951
- Oh.
- Yeah.

28:55.995 --> 28:57.344
My boyfriend's the maitre d'.

28:57.387 --> 28:58.606
He's a sweetheart

28:58.649 --> 29:00.608
and just an absolute dork.

29:00.651 --> 29:01.914
You would really like him.

29:01.957 --> 29:04.699
That's great, uh...

29:04.743 --> 29:06.788
I'm just so impressed.

29:06.832 --> 29:08.224
It seems like
you got everything

29:08.268 --> 29:09.617
you were hoping for
when you left Chicago.

29:09.660 --> 29:11.706
- It seems like
you're not doing

29:11.750 --> 29:12.968
too bad, either, yourself.

29:13.012 --> 29:14.143
I noticed on Facebook
you're with someone.

29:14.187 --> 29:15.405
- Yeah.

29:15.449 --> 29:17.886
- Yeah, Lily.

29:17.930 --> 29:20.062
She's--she's amazing.

29:20.106 --> 29:22.369
- Yeah, you two seem
so cute together.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.809
- It's really nice
to see you, Katie.

29:27.853 --> 29:30.420
I'm glad you came by.
- So am I.

29:33.293 --> 29:34.729
- Look who's here.

29:34.773 --> 29:36.731
- Hope I'm not
interrupting your lunch.

29:36.775 --> 29:38.298
Get over here.

29:38.341 --> 29:39.821
- Hi.
- Hey.

29:42.128 --> 29:43.303
- Good to see you.
- Good to see you too.

29:43.346 --> 29:44.739
- Yeah.

29:46.045 --> 29:48.134
- Hi.

29:48.177 --> 29:50.049
Oh, I can't believe
I finally get to meet you.

29:50.092 --> 29:52.355
I heard so much.
- Same here.

29:53.879 --> 29:55.445
I actually have something
you've been looking for.

29:55.489 --> 29:57.012
I hope I'm not too late.

29:57.056 --> 30:00.015
My mom told me that you
came by and tried to find it.

30:00.059 --> 30:03.192
My dad gave it to me a couple
years ago when we reconnected.

30:03.236 --> 30:05.499
He said he wanted me
to have something positive

30:05.542 --> 30:06.805
to remember him by.

30:09.242 --> 30:11.461
Is this what you've
been looking for?

30:11.505 --> 30:13.855
♪

30:13.899 --> 30:17.076
- Oh, my God, I--
Oh, I can't believe it.

30:17.119 --> 30:19.339
I was so scared that I was
gonna have to give up.

30:19.382 --> 30:22.385
I, um--oh, God!

30:22.429 --> 30:24.213
Katie, thank you.

30:24.257 --> 30:27.826
Oh, your brother needs this
so much right now.

30:27.869 --> 30:29.653
- You're welcome.
I'm glad I could help.

30:33.832 --> 30:35.442
Thank you.
- Yay!

30:36.138 --> 30:38.271
- When I started this shift,
I never thought I'd cross

30:38.314 --> 30:40.708
"false flag lawn-care ploy"
off my bucket list.

30:40.751 --> 30:42.579
- Every day is a gift.

30:45.452 --> 30:47.846
I'll catch up with you
at the rig, okay?

30:51.893 --> 30:55.549
Uh, Erica?

30:55.592 --> 30:57.072
- I'm Sylvie Brett.

30:57.116 --> 30:59.858
I treated you after
your accident the other day.

31:00.684 --> 31:02.686
- Right, um,
the ambulance driver.

31:02.730 --> 31:03.687
Um, I'm sorry.

31:03.731 --> 31:04.863
I wish I had time to talk,

31:04.906 --> 31:06.342
but I actually
am late to a class--

31:06.386 --> 31:09.389
- Were you texting
when the accident happened?

31:13.088 --> 31:16.962
- Your sister told me you
asked her to hold the phone.

31:17.005 --> 31:20.530
Did you do that to hide
what really happened?

31:21.836 --> 31:23.707
- No, I--that's not--

31:23.751 --> 31:26.580
- Look, I understand you're
afraid to tell the truth,

31:26.623 --> 31:28.060
scared about the consequences,

31:28.103 --> 31:31.019
but you need to realize,
the guilt you feel,

31:31.063 --> 31:32.325
it's not gonna go away

31:32.368 --> 31:33.935
just by pretending
it isn't there.

31:33.979 --> 31:36.242
♪

31:36.285 --> 31:38.548
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

31:38.592 --> 31:41.508
- Tell everyone
what really happened.

31:41.551 --> 31:45.251
Take responsibility now
so you can start making amends.

31:45.294 --> 31:47.470
The man you hit deserves that.

31:47.514 --> 31:50.386
♪

31:50.430 --> 31:51.822
So does your sister.

31:51.866 --> 31:59.047
♪

32:02.181 --> 32:03.617
- No, no, no, let me finish.

32:03.660 --> 32:05.532
You called me to say
the limo was confirmed,

32:05.575 --> 32:08.317
so I assumed
the limo was confirmed.

32:09.666 --> 32:11.538
Right, so what's the holdup?

32:13.148 --> 32:15.020
You know what, you--just stop.

32:15.063 --> 32:16.456
I'm gonna go with
another company.

32:16.499 --> 32:19.024
Yeah, fine, you do that.

32:28.033 --> 32:29.948
- One thing after another.

32:32.776 --> 32:34.648
- Let's take a deep breath.

32:34.691 --> 32:35.997
It'll all come together.

32:36.041 --> 32:37.607
- Yeah, maybe.

32:37.651 --> 32:40.001
- Kelly, look at me.

32:43.570 --> 32:47.008
Where is all this anger
taking you, huh?

32:47.052 --> 32:48.879
What's it for?

32:48.923 --> 32:51.360
- I'm not angry.
I'm just busy.

32:51.404 --> 32:53.928
♪

32:53.972 --> 32:56.017
- Kelly.

32:56.061 --> 32:58.889
He's not here anymore.

32:58.933 --> 33:02.806
Whatever he said to get
under your skin at the end,

33:02.850 --> 33:04.591
it's done.

33:04.634 --> 33:05.940
It's over.

33:05.984 --> 33:10.423
♪

33:10.466 --> 33:14.035
- The way we left things
the last time we talked,

33:14.079 --> 33:17.865
I took a jab at him,

33:17.908 --> 33:21.260
and he ended up
coming through anyway.

33:24.437 --> 33:26.221
- There's nothing
you could have said

33:26.265 --> 33:29.224
that would have
made this any easier.

33:29.268 --> 33:30.617
Nothing that
would have brought you

33:30.660 --> 33:32.488
the kind of peace
you're looking for.

33:34.621 --> 33:36.710
Right now, today,

33:36.753 --> 33:41.019
this is the start
of your life without your dad.

33:42.107 --> 33:44.718
How you live it,
that's what will define you.

33:47.764 --> 33:54.989
♪

34:10.309 --> 34:10.526
.

34:10.570 --> 34:12.702
- Thank you all for coming
this morning, thank you.

34:12.746 --> 34:14.965
Thanks for coming.
See you inside.

34:15.009 --> 34:16.532
Good morning, Sylvie.
- Good morning.

34:16.576 --> 34:18.360
Wow, you look nice.

34:18.404 --> 34:22.103
I mean, the stole
and everything is fancy.

34:22.147 --> 34:25.019
- You look nice too.

34:25.063 --> 34:26.716
Hey, how's your situation?

34:26.760 --> 34:29.110
Did that talk we had
help at all?

34:29.154 --> 34:30.851
- It did, yeah.

34:30.894 --> 34:33.506
I--I spoke to the driver,
told her what I knew.

34:33.549 --> 34:35.899
Urged her to clear
her conscience.

34:37.727 --> 34:41.122
- It took her a day to process,
but she came forward.

34:41.166 --> 34:44.125
- It sounds like the best
anyone could have hoped for.

34:44.169 --> 34:45.387
- Yeah, it is.

34:45.431 --> 34:47.346
Thank you for talking me
through it.

34:47.389 --> 34:50.218
- Oh, it's why I'm here.

34:50.262 --> 34:53.352
I hope you come by
and see me again.

34:53.395 --> 34:57.225
Um, you don't
have to wait for a crisis.

34:59.053 --> 35:00.228
- I might do that.

35:00.272 --> 35:02.230
♪

35:04.450 --> 35:11.674
♪

35:20.161 --> 35:22.903
- Hey, Stella.
- Hi.

35:22.946 --> 35:24.165
♪

35:24.209 --> 35:26.776
- Hey, sorry if I've been...

35:26.820 --> 35:28.865
- You don't need
to explain anything.

35:28.909 --> 35:31.433
♪

35:31.477 --> 35:34.001
I have something for you.

35:42.314 --> 35:43.445
- Thank you.

35:43.489 --> 35:50.757
♪

35:57.285 --> 35:59.592
- "Come to me, all who labor,

35:59.635 --> 36:03.465
"and are heavy-laden,
and I will give you rest.

36:03.509 --> 36:07.208
"Take my yolk upon you,
and learn from me,

36:07.252 --> 36:10.690
"for I am gentle
and lowly in heart,

36:10.733 --> 36:14.215
and you will find rest
for your souls."

36:14.259 --> 36:16.174
This is the word of the Lord.

36:16.217 --> 36:18.524
all: Amen.

36:36.150 --> 36:40.198
- My father was
a legendary firefighter.

36:40.241 --> 36:43.853
I know this because
he told me all the time.

36:47.422 --> 36:49.511
But he wasn't wrong.

36:50.425 --> 36:52.819
On March 16, 1993,

36:52.862 --> 36:57.302
he pulled seven people
out of the Paxton Hotel Fire.

36:57.345 --> 36:58.868
They were trapped,

36:58.912 --> 37:01.697
and nobody could figure out
how to get to them,

37:01.741 --> 37:04.222
but Benny wouldn't give up,

37:04.265 --> 37:06.572
even when the building
was coming down on top of him.

37:10.010 --> 37:12.708
That was Benny Severide.

37:12.752 --> 37:15.885
He always had to do
things his own way.

37:15.929 --> 37:22.065
He was stubborn,
and man, he was tough.

37:22.109 --> 37:24.329
Sometimes too tough.

37:24.372 --> 37:26.853
♪

37:26.896 --> 37:30.944
He'd battle the people he loved

37:30.987 --> 37:33.773
as hard as he'd battle
any fire.

37:35.122 --> 37:38.560
But every now and then,

37:38.604 --> 37:40.301
when you needed him the most,

37:40.345 --> 37:44.174
he'd have your back,
whether you knew it or not.

37:47.395 --> 37:49.310
No matter what the cost.

37:49.354 --> 37:52.313
♪

37:52.357 --> 37:54.576
It took me--

37:56.665 --> 37:59.189
It took me too long
to figure that out.

38:01.453 --> 38:03.716
But I'll never forget it.

38:06.980 --> 38:13.987
♪

38:32.353 --> 38:39.317
♪

38:39.360 --> 38:41.319
Sleep tight, Dad.

38:41.362 --> 38:43.669
You earned it.

38:44.539 --> 38:51.677
♪

39:02.514 --> 39:09.738
♪

39:29.758 --> 39:34.067
- Detail, attention!

39:34.110 --> 39:36.591
Present arms!

39:40.726 --> 39:43.337
Battalion Chief
Benjamin Severide

39:43.381 --> 39:45.252
has returned to quarters.

39:48.473 --> 39:55.697
♪

39:57.873 --> 40:00.572
He is cleared
from all his duties.

40:00.615 --> 40:03.575
He is gone,
but never forgotten.

40:03.618 --> 40:10.146
May he rest in peace with
his brothers and sisters above.

40:10.190 --> 40:12.235
- Ready.

40:12.279 --> 40:14.368
Step.

40:17.415 --> 40:24.596
♪

40:53.842 --> 41:01.110
♪
